From: Juergen Borleis <jbe@pengutronix.de>
Date: Mon, 23 Nov 2015 11:09:49 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Skov-DO63x: provide the most specific compatible string entry

Used to select the matching devicetree via bootspec and inside Barebox.
These specific strings are required to use one binary Barebox, one binary
Linux kernel and ony single root filesystem to support all boards.

Signed-off-by: Juergen Borleis <jbe@pengutronix.de>
---
 arch/arm/boot/dts/imx6dl-skov-dol63x-revA.dts | 2 +-
 arch/arm/boot/dts/imx6dl-skov-dol63x-revB.dts | 2 +-
